{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841299151,"sessionID":"ses_2879ce7dfffexdSxxBgGzWU26c","part":{"id":"prt_d7863a586001yrYgfglvZiV63d","messageID":"msg_d786395990013joySc3NmWJIZK","sessionID":"ses_2879ce7dfffexdSxxBgGzWU26c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_64f1ad8871ce4a7ca9d0613f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-004\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n### AR-004-001: Server initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a Go package at `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** creating HTTP server initialization\n- **THEN** the server SHALL embed necessary HTTP handlers\n- **AND** SHALL expose configurable listen address\n\n### AR-004-002: Health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server running\n- **WHEN** health check endpoint is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL return appropriate health status\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Workload Management API\n\n### AR-004-003: Create workload endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** HTTP server with workload management\n- **WHEN** POST request to create workload\n- **THEN** the workload SHALL be created successfully\n\n### AR-004-004: Get workload endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** existing workloads\n- **WHEN** GET request for specific workload\n- **THEN** it SHALL return workload details\n\n### AR-004-005: List workloads endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple workloads exist\n- **WHEN** GET request to list workloads\n- **THEN** it SHALL return all workloads\n\n---\n\n## References\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/openc